  "content": {
    "prompt": "<p><img alt=\"A graph plots a curve for x versus U of x. The horizontal axis lists the values from x subscript 0 through x subscript 3. The vertical axis ranges from negative 2.0 Joules to 1.0 Joule, in increments of 1.0. The curve starts from a point in the first quadrant before x subscript 1 on the horizontal axis and just before 1.0 J on the vertical axis. It declines to intersect the x-axis at the x subscript 0, then continues to decline below the x-axis till the point (x subscript 1, negative 2 Joules). The curve then rises to the first quadrant by intersecting the x-axis at x subscript 2. It then rises and extends horizontally through the point (x subscript 3, 0.5 Joules). All values are estimates.\" height=\"501\" src=\"/images/1a11befd2bce6d12cd6dbaf32bbc45ca.png\" width=\"330\"></p>\n\n<p>A conservative force has the potential energy function <em>U </em>( <em>x </em>), shown by the graph above. A particle moving in one dimension under the influence of this force has kinetic energy 1.0 joule when it is at position <em>x</em><sub>1</sub>. Which of the following is a correct statement about the motion of the particle?</p>\n",
